SB 1525-3
(LC 219)
2/9/26 (STN/ps)
Requested by SENATE COMMITTEE ON ENERGY AND ENVIRONMENT
PROPOSED AMENDMENTS TO
SENATE BILL 1525
1 On page 1 of the printed bill, delete lines 8 through 20 and insert:
2 “(2) The task force consists of no fewer than 13 members appointed as
3 follows:
4 “(a)(A) The President of the Senate shall appoint one member from among
5 the members of the Senate.
6 “(B) The Speaker of the House of Representatives shall appoint one
7 member from among members of the House of Representatives.
8 “(C) Of the members appointed under this paragraph, at least one shall
9 be a member of the coastal caucus.
10 “(b) The President and the Speaker shall jointly appoint not fewer than
11 10 members to represent:
12 “(A) Public and private research institutions;
13 “(B) Businesses innovating in blue economy sectors;
14 “(C) Commercial and noncommercial fishery businesses;
15 “(D) Recreational activities other than fishing;
16 “(E) The tourism industry;
17 “(F) Environmental organizations;
18 “(G) Equity investors in blue economy businesses;
19 “(H) Coastal labor;
20 “(I) The Sea Grant College of Oregon State University; and
21 “(J) Federally recognized Indian tribes located on the Oregon coast.

1 “(c) The chair of the Ocean Policy Advisory Council, or the chair’s
2 designee, shall serve as a member of the task force.”.
3 On page 2, delete lines 26 through 28 and insert:
4 “(10) The task force shall submit a report and may include recommen-
5 dations for legislation to the interim committees of the Legislative Assembly
6 related to the environment, in the manner provided by ORS 192.245, and to
7 the Ocean Policy Advisory Council, no later than September 15, 2027.”.
